Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 09, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
We all make mistakes and sometimes in our misguided attempt to navigate the guilt or ensure we won’t do it again, we punish ourselves. There are many ways we may punish ourselves, most commonly by saying mean or degrading things, constantly dredging up bad feelings or regrettable decisions so we can’t move on, not allowing ourselves to enjoy the good things in life, not allowing ourselves to have things we “don’t deserve” etc. It’s normal, it’s human, but it’s not helpful.

#millennialtherapist #sorry

node.text: Misguided efforts to save or preserve a relationship may end up doing just the opposite. #millennialtherapist #relationship

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'five things that won'tsave won' save your relationship @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Denying or ignoring problems. (Ignoring problems doesn't actually make them go away. Instead they often become bigger and more difficult to deal with) millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Ceasing to grow or change in order to maintain a status quo. (By limiting our growth, we limit the growth of our relationship. By not making space for our changes, we may slowly start to feel that the relationship is no longer a right fit for us) @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Lying in order to keep peace (Honesty promotes a healthy relationship -even ifit causes temporary discomfort) @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Guessing what the other person wants or needs. (The only way to know what the other person wants or needs is to ask them. Assumptions often lead to problems) @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Being someone other than yourself (If you need to be someone other than yourself in order for the relationship to function, you probably shouldn't be in that relationship) Sara Kuburic'.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'family boundaries can sound like: @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic'.

node.text: Family boundaries are often the hardest to set. These are just some general examples, every family dynamic will vary. (Read these with a respectful tone 😉). #millennialtherapist #family

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'family boundaries can sound like: @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic'.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I need you to respect my privacy. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Joking about my weight or relationship status hurts my feelings, I need you to stop. millennial.thrapst Sara Kuburic'.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I will no longer be the middle person in family arguments. @ millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Please stop asking when we will get married or have a kid, it's putting a lot of pressure on my relationship. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Our parent's divorce has been hard, and I refuse to take sides. @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic'.
Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I expect my partner to be treated with respect, or we will stop coming over. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I appreciate your feedback. It's important for me to be the one who decides how to raise my children. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I appreciate your willingness to help me, but please don't offer advice unless I ask for it. @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'stop expecting others to: @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic Know what you want without telling them Make decisions for you Never make mistakes Always agree with you Change (because you want them to) Be your source of happiness Fulfill all your needs Provide closure Always like you'.

node.text: We are often disappointed because people don’t/can’t live up to our expectations. Ensure that any expectation you set is realistic. #millennialtherapist #relationships

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text: Timing is important. Don’t rush or force things that are not meant for you right now ❤️ #millennialtherapist #relationships

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'reminder: @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic Whatever you're you feeling, it won't last forever.'.

node.text: An emotion won’t last forever (although sometimes it feels like it will). This is an important reminder not only when we are struggling, but also when we are experiencing something wonderful. The fact that emotions flow can encourage us to endure (the hard) and cherish (the good). #millennialtherapist #feelings

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'watch out for: @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic People who question your worth People who drain your energy People who don't celebrate your success People who don't support your healing People who take more than they give People who place unrealistic expectations on you People who cross your boundaries'.

node.text: Quick reminder: not everyone who wants be in your life deserves to be there. #millennialtherapist #people

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'non-physical compliments: @millennial.therapist/ Sara Kuburic |love how you don't jump to conclusions |love how you see the best in people love how you are brave enough to be yourself love how patient you are |love how funny you are |love how you approach people with empathy'.

Photo by Sara Kuburic on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'things that don't make you a failure: @millennial.therapist Sara Kuburic A relationship ending Not wanting the same things as everyone else •Changing your career Needing a break/rest Having others not validate your success'.

node.text: Let’s change the narrative around failing. Living life and making mistakes makes you human, not a failure ❤️ #millennialtherapist

Sara Kuburic Sometimes won't receive an apology that deserve. In those moments, will choose to validate my own feelings and give myself permission to close the chapter.'.

node.text:
I will not make my healing and growth dependent on someone else’s actions. 
#millennialtherapist #sorry
